{
  "description": {
    "title": "D1 two-market ONE-WAY linked golden: an upstream carbon price feeds a downstream sector's abatement cost through the mac_cost channel -- the acyclic template the D2 cyclic goldens mirror",
    "paper": "docs/platform-spec-d0-d1.md §2 (PriceLink semantics: additive-linear x_B(t) = x_B_base(t) + phi*P_A(t), contemporaneous, spec §2a/§2c), §2b (mac_cost channel shifts a targeted technology option's MAC price LEVEL), §3 (recursive-PE DAG, R34 -- no cycles in D1), §7 E4 (source's FINAL delivered path), E8 (horizon strict-subset). Engine: core/backend/engine/dispatch.py solve_multi_market_scenario + engine/links.py; channel: modules/market_links/backend/channels.py MacCostChannel.",
    "mechanism": "TWO competitive carbon markets solved as a one-way DAG. Market A ('upstream_ets') is the price SOURCE: a standalone cap-and-trade market with a three-tier threshold merit order (coal $20, gas $35, CCS $55 per tCO2e; each 100 tCO2e BAU, 40 tCO2e abatement capacity, zero free allocation). A tightening auction budget (270 -> 240 -> 200 tCO2e) walks the marginal abater up the merit order, so A clears at [20, 35, 55] over 2030-2032. Market B ('downstream_sector') is a downstream electrified sector whose single control option 'electrified_process' (base MAC $40/tCO2e, 60 tCO2e capacity on a 100 tCO2e plant, 70 tCO2e auctioned) has its marginal abatement COST raised by A's carbon price: x_B(t) = 40 + phi*P_A(t). The link is mac_cost with phi = 0.5 (each $1/tCO2e of upstream carbon price passes 0.5 into the downstream electrified process cost -- the power-price/carbon pass-through the electrified route embeds). B is the marginal abater, so B clears exactly at its shifted MAC level. A never sees B (one-way; no back-link -- a cycle would be D2 and the R34 DAG validator would reject it).",
    "inputs": "years 2030-2032; A: total_cap 300, auction_offered [270, 240, 200]; B: total_cap 100, auction_offered 70; both competitive, static (banking_allowed false), price_unit USD/tCO2e; single link upstream_ets -> downstream_sector, channel mac_cost, phi 0.5, target downstream_plant/electrified_process.",
    "expected_output": {
      "upstream_ets price 2030-2032 (SOURCE, unaffected by B)": [20.0, 35.0, 55.0],
      "downstream_sector price 2030-2032 (WITH link)": [50.0, 57.5, 67.5],
      "downstream_sector price 2030-2032 (B in ISOLATION, link stripped)": [40.0, 40.0, 40.0],
      "Link upstream_ets->downstream_sector Price In (= P_A(t))": [20.0, 35.0, 55.0],
      "Link upstream_ets->downstream_sector mac_cost Input Shift (= phi*P_A(t))": [10.0, 17.5, 27.5],
      "hand check": "B's shifted MAC intercept = base 40 + phi*P_A(t); B is the marginal abater so the clearing price equals that intercept: 40 + 0.5*[20,35,55] = [50, 57.5, 67.5], matching the WITH-link path. The link bite (WITH minus ISOLATION) is [10, 17.5, 27.5] -- material at every year. A is byte-identical whether or not the link/B is present (recursive-PE: the source solves first with no inbound edge).",
      "note": "Prices land within ~1e-12 of the stated round numbers (Brent's method lands on the threshold discontinuity where B's abatement flips 0 -> 60 tCO2e); atol 1e-6 in the anchor test. Composite result keys: '<scenario> :: upstream_ets' and '<scenario> :: downstream_sector'."
    },
    "run": "uv run python -m pe.cli --config examples/showcase_two_market_link.json"
  },
